(939, NULL, 'This year\'s ARTWALK NY honoring Louise Fishman and Vincent and Shelly Fremont takes place on November 29, 2017 at Spring Studios, located at 50 Varick Street.', 'artwalkny@cfthomeless.org', NULL, 'New York', 'United States', '10013', 'Nonprofit Organization', NULL, 'SAVE THE DATE: The 23rd Annual ARTWALK NY honoring Louise Fishman and Vincent and Shelly Fremont is November 29, 2017.\n\nPresented by MaxMara\n\nFeaturing works from more than 100 artists.\n\n6:30 PM Silent Auction | 8:00 PM Live Auction\nSpring Studios | 50 Varick St | New York City\n\nPlease join us on November 29th for the 23rd Annual ARTWALK NY âx80x93 New York\'s premier chartiy art auction. ARTWALK NY brings together artists, art lovers and other compassionate New Yorkers at this exciting event to celebrate the role of "artist-as-activist" and increase critical attention to the issues of homelessness, poverty and social injustice.\n\nTonight, more than 61,000 New Yorkers, including 23,000 children, will sleep in homeless shelters.\n\nThe Coalition for the Homeless provides emergency food and clothing, eviction prevention, crisis services, permanent housing, job training adn special programs for kids for over 3,500 New Yorkers each day. For more than 35 years, we\'ve been helping homeless men, women and children find their way to a safe, stable home.\n', 453273),
