(1322, NULL, 'Semi-precious gemstone sterling silver jewellery. Designed in Scotland.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jewelry/Watches', NULL, 'Our striking jewellery designs combined with natural organic semi precious gemstones are inspired by the colours of the stunning coastal region of Moray in North East Scotland with beautiful heather clad mountains, hills and coastal paths, stunning golden sand beaches all beside the clear Moray Firth.\n\nThe use of only hand selected, natural organic rough semi precious gemstones set in sterling silver is what makes every single piece of jewellery completely unique. Aquamarine, amethyst, tanzanite and ruby are just a few of the semi precious stones we use in our collections.\n\nThe beautiful stones we use are sourced from Africa, Asia and South America including Tanzania, Madagascar and Brazil. Not only are our gemstones sourced from such amazing locations we use centuries old techniques and traditional skills to set these perfect stones into our handmade jewellery.\n\nOur product range consists of earrings, necklaces, bracelets, cufflinks, pendants and our matching sets. But don\'t be fooled, each piece is unique and different to the rest. So be assured your item will be not only be handmade but will be one of a kind.\n\nWe are registered with the Edinburgh Assay Hallmarking Office and our pieces are hallmarked where appropriate.', 410740);

